19/06/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The 8th international conference of the Balkan Political Club was held in Sofia at the weekend. 
The club is an initiative of former Bulgarian President Zhelyu Zhelev, bringing together other former top political leaders and intellectuals from Balkan countries. 
This time, participants discussed major infrastructure projects and how their implementation could be accelerated. 
They agreed that a modern and well-developed infrastructure in the region would boost security and the EU integration prospects of these states. 
(Monitor - 19/06/05; bTV, BNR - 18/06/05)
